**Emergency Steps:**  
- Use a cell phone or hard-wired phone to report outages or emergencies.  
- Use battery-operated flashlights instead of candles to prevent fire hazards.  
- Unplug or turn off all electric appliances to avoid power surges when electricity is restored.  
- Keep refrigerator and freezer doors closed to preserve food for as long as possible.  
- Stay informed about the outage by checking updates on PG&E's website or social media channels.

**Non-Emergency Tips:**  
- Secure helium-filled metallic balloons with weights to prevent them from floating into power lines and causing outages.  
- Learn how to sign up for power shutoff notifications to stay informed about planned outages.  
- Discover ways to save energy and reduce your bill by following PG&E's summer energy-saving tips available on their website.  

For more information, you can visit the [City of San José's utility company listings](https://www.sanjoseca.gov/your-government/departments-offices/public-works/development-services/utilities-section/utility-company-listings) or the [PG&E Public Safety Power Shutoffs page](https://www.sanjoseca.gov/your-government/departments-offices/office-of-the-city-manager/emergency-management/be-prepared/pg-e-public-safety-power-shutoffs).